<br>
- SW:G is coming soon and they want to charge $15+ for it a month, so this increase will be a bridge. People won't be all outraged at a 50% price hike per month when galaxies comes out<br>
<br>
- Resource cost is probably high right now because they want to deliver the next expansion quickly and with a lot of content. They realize the high level people eat up content REALLY fast. So they need to budget content developers, the live team, and a team of people to improve the stability and quality of the internal game stuff (i.e. bazaar, new interface, etc).<br>
<br>
- Morale is pretty high right now with a lot of longstanding issues being addressed lately.<br>
<br>
- I would also think they realize now that having legends only functionality that is back filled to all servers months after it goes live on legends isn't sitting well. So they'd like to spread out the costs to everyone and bring new features to all servers faster<br>
<br>
Those are just my thoughts. This is like when Tivo raised rates. I get my moneys worth at the old price and with the new price, so as much as it is frustrating, it's worth it to me.<br>
